<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870202-0153 </DOCNO><HL> Wells Fargo Stock OpensFor Amex Options Trades</HL><DD> 02/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WFCSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The American Stock Exchange opened put and call options trading in the stock of Wells Fargo andamp; Co., a San Francisco-based bank holding company.    Wells Fargo succeeds Revco D.S. Inc., which went private last month in a management-led leveraged buyout.    Initial expiration months for the Wells Fargo options are February, March, April and July. Position and exercise limits are 3,000 contracts on the same side of the market.    Options are securities that grant the holder the right, but not the obligation, to buy or sell 100 shares of a stock by a certain date and at a specified price. Calls are options to buy stock, and puts are options to sell. </TEXT></DOC>